Vea Victis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nydia>Nydia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/25/01 12:08:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=76>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> I'm so used to running/boating everywhere I go (and with the<br>
introduction of luclin, travel time can be cut down considerably with creative nexus usage), that I rarely use port services.  But on the rare occasion that I have needed <br>
one (to help guild party post-wipeout, etc), I just put a shout out and, once I get a response, ask if 20-30pp is okay.  If I don't get a response, I just keep on moving, and try again in the next zone.  Few things irritate me more than folks standing about for 30 minutes + shouting for a TP to a locale a few zones away, when if they'd just been willing to use their feet they could have already been there....  <br>
<br>
It seems that is is only common courtesy to offer the druid/wiz something for their trouble; after all, it is their time and mana.  I *don't* shout out with a cash offer; as someone said above, if someone is busy, they're busy, and I'd just as soon not bother them. (and, if they're *only* in it for the money, I'd just as soon not use their services)<br>
<br>
As far as rezzes go, I *always* offer to pay the cleric for these.  A rez takes a lot more out of the cleric and his party's time under most circumstances than a port, and most likely at the time you need one, there aren't very many clerics standing around with nothing better to do.  I also always offer to drag the corpse to the cleric, if possible, than ask him to come to it.  Many clerics are perpetually 'in the hole' anyway due to using symbol, etc (over 50% of Faervas' and my income right now (L 47) currently goes to keeping us in rune/symbol gems), which they are expected to do, so I think of 100pp or so as an appropriate donation for a 49+ rez, less for a 39...  if he's in the party, of course, the rezzes are gratis; this is for 'request' rezzes...  <br>
<br>
I am neither a druid, wizard, or cleric, so I am not one to talk in these matters, but I do think it is nice to do 'pro bono' work every once in a while, helping out lower level characters in these matters, I usually slap clarity/augmentation on lowbies I see when passing through the oasis/town gates, etc.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cp,<br>
Nydia Ywalmoriel<br>
