<br>
If i am in a group I generally ask the group members if it is ok that I rez someone who needs it and I split any donation with everyone in the party (as me rezing is infringing on their gaming time as well as mine if I am the primary healer). <br>
<br>
Guildies and friends always get free rezes, of course.<br>
<br>
I think it generally comes down to a combination of courtesy and time.  People want rezes and TPs to save their time (understandable), unfortunatly this usually costs another player time (for travel, mana recovery, etc).<br>
<br>
I personally always donate for rezes and TPs when not asking guildies. To me it just seems courteous to repay people for their effort and time (PP is just one method of this,  kind words, buffs and othersuch work as well, but nothing seems as appreciated as the almighty dollar, so  I make sure to include PP as well as the others) <p><img src="http://www.calamity.net/kfw/upload_repository/baynesig2c.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uclanmcstump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ClanMcStump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/26/01 5:07:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=78>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> Regardless of whether I am in a hurry or not, I pay 100p for a Teleport.  If I need one, I usually dont bother my guild for it (unless its for a raid) I just sit at a druid or wizard Teleporter and Shout &quot;Paying well for a port to...&quot;  and usually I am where I need to be in less than 5 minutes.<br>
